sir archibald mitchelson, 1st baronet (died december 1945) was a british investment banker. he was chairman of mitchelson partners ltd, as well as d. davis & sons ltd, the shipbuilders j. samuel white & co ltd, old silkstone collieries ltd, admiralty collieries ltd, north's navigation collieries ltd, wharncliffe collieries ltd, yorkshire collieries ltd, great universal stores ltd, anglo-continental guano works ltd, pangnga river tin concessions ltd, genatosan ltd, and kamunting tin dredging ltd. he was also president of porcupine-davidson gold mines ltd of ontario and a director of a number of other companies. he was created a baronet in the 1920 birthday honours.